ess, operating system and version, screen resolution, device type, manufacturer and model, language, browser type and version. We also collect user history of Website access, service, and activity, including dates and times of sign-ins, user profile, and any agreements with, request for, submission of, or interaction with content represented or provided within the Website.</p>\n <p>Website Analytics Information Collected Automatically. We also automatically collect device and browser information related to your interaction with the Website including IP address, operating system and version, screen resolution, device type, manufacturer and model, language, browser type and version (<strong>\u201cAnalytics Information\u201d</strong>). The Analytics Information we collect includes the history of Website access, service, and activity, including dates and times of sign-ins, user profile, and any agreements with, request for, submission of, or interaction with content represented or provided within the Website. We use cookies as part of the technology used to collect the Analytics Information.</p>\n <p><strong>Access to, Correction and Deletion of Personal Information</strong></p>\n <p>The Website allows you to access, review and modify business and any related Personal Information you provide in connection with your use of the Website. You may also have the right under applicable state or federal law to request that we delete certain Personal Information we have about you. Otherwise, you may submit an access request to us by creating a support request to update or modify the information you provide. Schwab will retain your business information and any related Personal Information for auditing purposes, to troubleshoot problems, enforce our policies, and comply with corporate standards and legal requirements. We will retain this Personal Information so long as permitted by applicable law, and will delete this information when required by applicable law.</p>\n <p>Once we receive and confirm your verifiable consumer request, we will disclose to you:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The categories of Personal Information we collected about you.</li>\n<li>The categories of sources for the Personal Information we collected about you.</li>\n<li>Our business or commercial purpose for collecting that Personal Information.</li>\n<li>The categories of third parties with whom we share that Personal Information.</li>\n<li>The specific pieces of Personal Information we collected about you</li>\n<li>If we disclosed your Personal Information for a business purpose, we will identify the Personal Information categories that each category of recipient obtained.</li>\n  </ul>\n <p><strong>How we use and share information</strong></p>\n <p>Our Business Use. We use the information you provide to consider your eligibility for Website, including the Developer Program, access and information, identity authentication, and to fulfill your requests and support your interaction with the Website. Uses of this information also include operational messaging and administrative communications, such as user auditing, alerts, responding to support requests, and changes to our terms, conditions, and policies. </p>\n <p>Not Responsible for Third Parties. We are not responsible for the collection or use of your information by any other organization, including any business and related Personal Information you disclose to other organizations through or in connection with the Website.</p>\n <p>Service Providers. We may also provide your information to our third-party service providers to support our business operations, the Developer Program and your interaction with the Website. We enter contracts with our third-party service providers that describe the purpose of their use, and requires them to both keep that Personal Information confidential, and to not use it for any purpose except performing their contract with us and performing services for us.</p>\n<p>We will use your information to comply with applicable law or other legal obligations. We use your information as directed by you.</p>\n<p>Do Not Sell or Share for Tracking or Advertising. We do not sell your personal information, or share it for tracking or advertising purposes (e.g., through ad networks for personalized or interest-based advertising, or targeting of advertising based on your personal information).</p>\n <p><strong>Data Security</strong></p>\n <p>We have taken steps and implemented administrative, technical, and physical safeguards designed to protect against the risk of accidental, intentional, unlawful, or unauthorized access, alteration, destruction, disclosure, or use. The Internet is not 100% secure and we cannot guarantee the security of information transmitted through the Internet. Where you have been given or you have chosen a password, it is your responsibility to keep this password confidential</p>\n <p><strong>Individuals in the European Economic Area (EEA)</strong></p>\n <p>All data is stored and processed in the United States. By using and accessing our site, users who reside or are located in countries outside of the United States agree and consent to the transfer to and processing of personal information on servers located outside of the country where they reside, and that the protection of such information may be different than required under the laws of their residence or location. For additional information on how we treat personal data of individuals in the EEA please go to Schwab\u2019s General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) Privacy Notice located here: https://www.schwab.com/public/file/-P-11143694</p>\n <p><strong>Use of the Website by minors</strong></p>\n <p>Individuals under the age of 13 are not permitted to use the Website.</p>\n",this.translationKeysService.getKeys().pipe((0,or.s)(1)).subscribe(a=>{this.translations=a})}static{this.\u0275fac=function(p){return new(p||y)(i.rXU(Jt.b))}}static{this.\u0275cmp=i.VBU({type:y,selectors:[["privacy-policy"]]